        "created_at": "2025-06-08T20:39:49.509Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I’m on v7.43.1 stable from Play Store. Last night I wanted to post a story about the latest stable version update. After I chose all Signal connections, I pressed post and it got stuck on sending. I deleted the post and now Signal closes very soon after I open it. Maybe this happened because I had a hotspot enabled from my mobile data?<br>\nAt one point I turned off mobile data and Signal stopped crashing. I should have taken a debug log then. I guess I’ll have to wait until the next stable update to check if it gets fixed.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Edit: should I clear cache in App info?</p>\n<p>Copied from my hidden post here: <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/beta-feedback-for-the-upcoming-android-7-44-release/69563/12\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Beta feedback for the upcoming Android 7.44 release - #12 by Aku-Stable</a><br>\n(Originally posted 11 hours ago)</p>",
