    "username": "Aku-Stable",
    "name": "",
    "excerpt": "<p>Debug Log: <a href=\"https://debuglogs.org/android/7.43.1/2135be88d0960201393f916b13988486f2152196b641f2b0b6d73883a1b25048\">https://debuglogs.org/android/7.43.1/2135be88d0960201393f916b13988486f2152196b641f2b0b6d73883a1b25048</a></p>\n<p>Now Signal is working fine!<br>\nI think it’s because 24 hours has passed since I first tried to post a story. Maybe Signal was stuck in a crash loop trying to post the original image.<br>\nTurning off mobile data and/or hotspot didn’t help.<br>\nAnd turning on airplane mode didn’t help either.</p>\n<p><a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/cody-signal\">@cody-signal</a>, could you check this, maybe prevent it happening to someone else?</p>\n<p>Hopefully anyone else having this same problem sees this post/topic and doesn’t end up clearing storage in app info, or uninstalling Signal which would delete all their messages and media!</p>"
